Hello
It is, did you update to the latest moose? We only added this recently.
In FVDiffusion you can see:
  const auto & interp_method = getParam<MooseEnum>("coeff_interp_method");
  if (interp_method == "average")
    _coeff_interp_method = Moose::FV::InterpMethod::Average;
  else if (interp_method == "harmonic")
    _coeff_interp_method = Moose::FV::InterpMethod::HarmonicAverage;

It's weird (to me, at least): if I add "harmonic" to the interp_method, the code throws and error:  Invalid option "harmonic" in MooseEnum. Valid options (not case-sensitive) are "average"". What is weird is that I pulled and build a new distribution and there are FV kernels like FVDiffusion that include "harmonic" as an option to interp_method. I use exactly the same syntax as in, eg FVDiffusion or FVAnisotropicDiffusion: in validParams I have
MooseEnum coeff_interp_method("average harmonic","average");
paras.addParam<MooseEnum>("coeff_interp_method", coeff_interp_method, "Switch to select interpolation method");

That seems to be what throws the error. If I change to
MooseEnum coeff_interp_method("average");
paras.addParam<MooseEnum>("coeff_interp_method", coeff_interp_method, "Switch to select interpolation method");

then I do not get the error. What is even weirder is that the error shows up even when I do not include this particular kernel in the input file.

Hi Guillaume,

Below are the relevant code lines. When I have commented out the lines with
"harmonic", it works. When I put those lines back in (and comment out the
lines with just "average"), execution throws an error, even if I do not use
this kernel in the execution.

```
InputParameters
FVMagneticExchangeNonCons::validParams()
{
  InputParameters params = FVFluxKernel::validParams();
  params.addClassDescription("Computes residual of conservative exchange
torque");
  params.addRequiredParam<unsigned int>("component", "An integer
corresponding to the direction in order parameter space");
  params.addRequiredCoupledVar("mag_x", "The x component of the constrained
magnetic vector");
  params.addRequiredCoupledVar("mag_y", "The y component of the constrained
magnetic vector");
  params.addRequiredCoupledVar("mag_z", "The z component of the constrained
magnetic vector");
  MooseEnum coeff_interp_method("average");
  //  MooseEnum coeff_interp_method("average harmonic", "harmonic");
  params.addParam<MooseEnum>(
    "coeff_interp_method",
    coeff_interp_method,
    "Switch that can select interpolation method for magnetization
density.");
  params.set<unsigned short>("ghost_layers") = 2;
  return params;
}
```

